},
    {
      "text": "But time glides on and still no sound of the wheels of thy chariot. Many a procession passes by with noise and shouts and glamour of glory. Is it only thou who wouldst stand in the shadow silent and behind them all? And only I who would wait and weep and wear out my heart in vain longing?",
      "source": "Rabindranath Tagore",
      "id": 7763,
      "length": 291
    }
